cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI

The paper deals with detecting the internal structure of a system using experimental methods, which is a topic related to system identification and control. Therefore, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of linear approximation and varying excitation signals, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with nonlinear systems, which is a topic related to neural networks and computational neuroscience, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the use of frequency response functions, which is a topic related to signal processing, making cs.SI (Signal Processing) a possible sub-category.
